<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
  <li>1.5 kg (3.3 lbs) bone-in gammon joint</li>
  <li>1 onion, peeled and halved</li>
  <li>2 liters (8 cups) Coca-Cola</li>
  <li>1 cinnamon stick</li>
  <li>1 star anise</li>
  <li>1 teaspoon whole cloves</li>
  <li>200g (1 cup) light brown sugar</li>
  <li>2 tablespoons Dijon mustard</li>
  <li>Zest and juice of 1 orange</li>
  <li>2 tablespoons malt vinegar</li>
  </ul>
<h2>Method</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Place the gammon joint in a large pot, add the onion, and pour in enough Coca-Cola to cover the meat. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 1 hour.</li>
  <li>Preheat the oven to 180°C (160°C fan or Gas Mark 4).</li>
  <li>Remove the gammon from the pot, discarding the cooking liquid and onion. Score the fat in a diamond pattern.</li>
  <li>In a small saucepan, combine the remaining Coca-Cola, brown sugar, mustard, cinnamon stick, star anise, whole cloves, orange zest, orange juice, and malt vinegar. Simmer over medium heat for 15-20 minutes, or until the mixture thickens into a glossy glaze.</li>
  <li>Place the gammon in a roasting pan and pour half of the glaze over the top, making sure to get it into the scored lines.</li>
  <li>Roast the gammon in the preheated oven for about 30 minutes, basting with the remaining glaze every 10 minutes.</li>
  <li>Once the gammon is caramelized and golden, remove it from the oven. Allow it to rest for a few minutes before slicing.</li>
</ol>
